2019 is off to a great start for Lucara Diamond Corp, with the Canada-headquartered mining company having recovered another large diamond at its Karowe mine, in Botswana. The large find is a 223 ct, high white gem diamond, which will be shown alongside the 240 ct and 127 ct top white gem diamonds found last month, at the upcoming March 7 tender. Lucara is listed on the TSX.